  "vulnerability_information": "libcurl provides several different backends for resolving host names, selected at build time. If it is built to use the synchronous resolver, it allows name resolves to time-out slow operations using alarm() and siglongjmp().\n\nWhen doing this, libcurl used a global buffer that was not mutex protected and a multi-threaded application might therefore crash or otherwise misbehave.\n\n## Impact\n\nDenial of service due to a crash (likely) or possibly other impacts.",
